#. <section class="sutta" id="sn15.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn15.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 15"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 15"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 1. Paṭhamavagga → tiṇakaṭṭhavaggo (bj)
msgctxt "sn15.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn15.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Tiṇakaṭṭhasutta"
msgstr "1. Grass and Sticks"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.178"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn15.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

# See BB’s note on anamatagga, and my note at https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-the-unknowability-of-sa-sara/2859<a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. </p><p>
#. VAR: Anamataggoyaṃ → anamataggāyaṃ (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn15.1:1.7"
msgid "“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro."
msgstr "“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning."

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.8"
msgid ""
"Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ "
"sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ."
msgstr ""
"No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, "
"hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving."

# PTS has “a stack of squares” for caturangala, while BB curiously enough omits it entirely. But surely the meaning is as I have here. “small stick, tig” is a recognized meaning of ghatika.
#. VAR: taṃ chetvā → tacchetvā (si, s1-3, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn15.1:1.9"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso yaṃ imasmiṃ jambudīpe tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ "
"taṃ chetvā ekajjhaṃ saṃharitvā caturaṅgulaṃ caturaṅgulaṃ ghaṭikaṃ katvā "
"nikkhipeyya:"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to strip all the grass, sticks, branches, and leaves in "
"India, gather them together into one pile, and chop them each into four inch "
"pieces. They’d lay them down, saying:"

#. VAR: apariyādinnāva → apariyādinnā ca (s1-3, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn15.1:1.10"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ me mātā, tassā me mātu ayaṃ mātā’ti, apariyādinnāva, bhikkhave, tassa "
"purisassa mātumātaro assu, atha imasmiṃ jambudīpe tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ "
"parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"‘This is my mother, this is my grandmother.’ The grass, sticks, branches, "
"and leaves of India would run out before that person’s mothers and "
"grandmothers."

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.11"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.12"
msgid "Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro."
msgstr "Transmigration has no known beginning."

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.13"
msgid ""
"Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ "
"sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ."
msgstr ""
"No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, "
"hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving."

#. VAR: kaṭasī → kaṭasi (bj, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn15.1:1.14"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ tibbaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ "
"byasanaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ, kaṭasī vaḍḍhitā."
msgstr ""
"For such a long time you have undergone suffering, agony, and disaster, "
"swelling the cemeteries."

msgctxt "sn15.1:1.15"
msgid ""
"Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ alaṃ virajjituṃ "
"alaṃ vimuccitun”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and "
"freed regarding all conditions.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn15.1:1.16"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
